rComments: He was a very interesting prof! Very patriotic and his classes were fun.

Such an awesome professor, he was extremely nice and VERY understanding if something was missed. Only issue is that he is very scattered with his syllabus but if you talk to him one on one he clarifies everything. He also speaks a bit of broken english, but assignments are so easy for his class.

He is so full of historical and fun facts about the Portuguese speaking countries and has a good sense of humour. He is very easy going when it comes to grading and handing in paper. I highly recommend him for an elective. Only issue is his syllabus is all over the place.

I found it to be all over the place sometimes, BUT he's very nice and approachable, and he'll try his best to make you understand! Although I was very lost and basically didn't understand that much, the midterms have been quite easy (with very little study!) and we had a take-home final! The extras were also very nice (movies, piano concert etc.)!
Great Professor, helps his students and everything is clear!
Legit the worst prof I have ever had. Made me want to jump out a window. So boring and dry. Avoid at all costs
Great professor! Very knowledgeable about the Portuguese speaking world!

Worst most boring prof I have ever had. Plus he can be elitist, thinking everything from Portugal is better than the other Portuguese speaking countries. Nothing is ever interesting in this class, and all he does is just mutter on about NOTHING. Worst class ever

He is very enthusiastic, good humoured and loves to discuss with the class. The material is very interesting- everyone should take his class if you need an elective. Sometimes the lectures are boring though, especially if he reads from the page.
